It all started when Malala Yousafza was a Pakistani girl, she was 11 years old, she liked, like all children of that age, to play, go out, watch her favorite program and, she watched a program where her protagonist had a magic pencil with which she could appear food if she was hungry or even save her and her friends from some danger, she wanted and dreamed of a pencil to be able to put a lock on her door so that her brothers would stop bothering her for a while, she wanted to be able to stop time for a little longer to stay in bed in the morning and better yet, erase the bad smell that came from the garbage dump near her house, make dresses for her mother, school for her father or a ball for her brothers. Over time she realized that the reality in which she lived was very harsh, and this was one day that she was walking near the garbage dump of her house, and she saw that a girl her age was looking through the garbage, that was when she realized She notes that not all children in her country had access to education. With the arrival of the Taliban to power, she experienced a complete change from her childhood, including her life, as girls were prohibited from going to school. but malala was not ready to be defeated, so she decided to fight for the right of girls to study. In 2009, she created a blog commenting that everyone should have the right to education; Through the blog, many people knew her and she was even interviewed on television in various countries. soon she and her family began to receive threats, but malala yousafza and her family did not give up. One day, Malala was in a truck and a man with his face covered approached him and shot him. Malala was seriously injured, but fortunately she was saved. She had to leave her country, but from abroad she continues to fight for the right to education for boys and girls. Malala's voice went very far, and today she is a UN peace messenger, she continues the fight for the rights of children who are not in school, she is an international icon and is even the youngest person in have received the Nobel Peace Prize. discovered that each pencil is magical if used in the right way, this can contribute to building a world of peace.

mediante el blog muchas personas la conocieron e incluso fue entrevistada en la televisión de varios países. pronto ella y su familia comenzaron a recibir amenazas, pero malala yousafza y su familia no se rindieron. un día, malala iba en un camión y un señor con la cara cubierta lo abordó y le disparó. malala resultó gravemente herida, pero por fortuna pudo salvarse. ella tuvo que salir de su país, pero desde el extranjero sigue luchando por el derecho a la educación de niños y niñas. la voz de malala llegó muy lejos, y hoy en día es mensajera de la paz de la ONU, ella continúa con la lucha por los derechos de los niños que no están escolarizados, ella es un ícono internacional e incluso es la persona más joven en haber recibido el premio nobel de la paz. descubrió que cada lápiz es mágico si se usa de la manera correcta, esto puede contribuir a construir un mundo de paz.
